<p>Traditional forced-air systems with high-efficiency gas furnaces (90%+ AFUE) paired with central air conditioning units (14+ SEER) also work well in Salem's climate. Given the moderate heating and cooling demands, homeowners should focus on properly sized systems rather than oversized units that cycle frequently and waste energy. Ductless mini-split systems are gaining popularity in Salem, especially for homes without existing ductwork or for room additions, offering zone control that works well with the area's mild climate variations throughout the seasons.</p>

