<p>South Salem neighborhoods like Morningside and Candalaria offer predominantly single-family homes built in the 1970s-1990s, making them ideal candidates for both solar installation and HVAC upgrades. These areas typically have the roof space and electrical infrastructure needed for residential solar systems. Northeast Salem, including areas near Lancaster Drive, features more affordable housing stock where solar and efficient HVAC systems can provide particularly strong value through reduced utility costs. The newer developments in Keizer and surrounding areas often come with modern HVAC systems but present excellent opportunities for solar installation on newer roofs with good structural integrity.</p>

